Horrible New England conditions. Icy roads. Windy as fuck. The snow was lowk nice tho. In the middle of my run my foot went numb and genuinely thought I broke it. It was like my right foot was stepping on a ball the entire time. Phone crashed because of the cold and then died. Watch kept tracking while charging and dead for some reason so pace is fucked. It didn’t track the full mileage. But at the end of it all, pretty happy bc I ran today :)
It was only 14 degrees and parents were dropping their kids off to the beginning of their street. Games gone soft.
Back bi with dad was fire
I wanted to go further but I almost slipped like 5 times bc of black ice. I told myself I gotta study so that’s what we on. Plank time: 1 min

- the target bathrooms are pretty clean (target)

This album feeds my future generations. I believe that this is his undeniably his best work. I haven’t heard better bars in my life. And genuinely, it was everything I’ve ever wanted. This is him at his true peak on lyricism, flow, bars. When an artist says that an album defines them, usually it’s only a few songs but it’s just J Cole on this. Like he provides a perfect critique on rap, confidence, braggadociousness, establishing his pinnacle on the top of the rap game, competitiveness to the best, his come up and many more themes that truly define what rap is. It is perfect hip hop. T-minus’s influence on the production definitely the best he’s ever been. This album is PURE rap. I understand I am biased but genuinely incredible. If I had to show someone that doesn’t know what rap has to offer, I’d ask them to listen to this album.
